  "body": "# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWhen too many validators are managed by a validator client, the body of [/eth/v1/builder/validators ](https://ethereum.github.io/builder-specs/#/Builder/registerValidator) can be quite heavy.\r\n\r\nThe majority of `mainnet` relays does support heavy `registerValidator` bodies. However, some others do not and sometimes:\r\n- timeout\r\n- return an error\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\nThe Prysm validator client could expose a `--validator-registration-batch-size <size>` flag.\r\n(The name of the flag is the same as in Lighthouse.)\r\n\r\nWhen activated, this flag will batch registration requests into multiple calls of `<size>` items maximum.\r\n\r\n### Describe alternatives you've considered\r\n\r\nReduce the number of validators per validator client. (And so increase the number of validator clients.)\r\n",
